headline: U.S. shoppers spend $1.5 trillion a year. Here’s which retailers win – Bernstein
summary: Investing.com -- As U.S. consumers pour more than $1.5 trillion annually into packaged food, drinks, and household essentials, retailers like Walmart (NYSE:WMT) and Costco (NASDAQ:COST) are emerging as the biggest winners, Bernstein said.
